      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is acting weird. the fan is making this constant humming sound but the blades arent actually spinning. i can hear the motor trying to work but nothing is moving. what is probably wrong with it and what should i do before i try to look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A humming motor without spinning blades is a classic symptom of a faulty capacitor, which is a crucial component in most AC units. You can try to diagnose the issue by checking the capacitor first, but be careful not to get electrocuted. It's a good idea to turn off the power to the unit at the circuit breaker before attempting any repairs. Make sure to verify the unit is completely dead before starting work on it. \n\nIt's also possible that the capacitor is blown, which can be a sign of a more serious electrical issue. If you're not comfortable with DIY repairs, it's recommended to call a professional electrician to inspect and fix the unit. They'll be able to assess the situation and provide a more accurate diagnosis. \n\nIn the meantime, you can try to identify the type of capacitor used in your AC unit by checking the unit's documentation or searching online for the specific model. Some common types of capacitors include electrolytic, film, and ceramic. \n\nIt's also worth noting that a faulty capacitor can cause other issues, such as overheating, reduced airflow, and increased energy bills. So, addressing the problem promptly is essential to prevent further damage and ensure your unit operates efficiently.",
